What is event bubbling  in LWC ?
Companies that asked this: Salesforce, IBM, TCS, Microsoft, Accenture

Answer:
Event bubbling is the process where an event originates from a child component or element and then propagates upward through its parent components.

In LWC, when you dispatch a custom event with bubbles: true, it can be caught by parent components in the DOM tree.


Example

Child component dispatches a CustomEvent('notify') with { bubbles: true }.

Parent component listens for the onnotify event using native HTML syntax.

childComponent.js

import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
 
export default class ChildComponent extends LightningElement {
    handleClick() {
        // Dispatch a bubbling event
        this.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('notify', {
            bubbles: true,
            detail: { message: 'Child says hello!' }
        }));
    }
}
2. childComponent.html

<template>
    <button onclick={handleClick}>Notify Parent</button>
</template>


3. parentComponent.html

<template>
    <div onnotify={handleNotify}>
        <c-child-component></c-child-component>
    </div>
</template>

4. parentComponent.js

import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
 
export default class ParentComponent extends LightningElement {
    handleNotify(event) {
        alert(`Received from child: ${event.detail.message}`);
    }
}
The event will bubble up from child to parent inside the shadow DOM, so parent can handle it.

The event will not cross the shadow DOM boundary, so grandparent cannot handle it.
